note_quality.structure: Notes should have clear headings, logical flow, and proper organization
note_quality.completeness: All key concepts and main topics should be covered
note_quality.accuracy: Information should be factually correct and well-explained
note_quality.clarity: Notes should be easy to understand and student-friendly

study_materials.quiz_quality: Questions should be relevant, challenging but fair, with clear explanations
study_materials.flashcard_effectiveness: Cards should cover key terms and concepts for effective memorization
study_materials.summary_completeness: Summary should capture all important points concisely
study_materials.action_items_practicality: Action items should be specific, actionable, and relevant

content_processing.audio_transcription: Audio content should be accurately transcribed and processed
content_processing.video_analysis: Video content should be properly analyzed for educational value
content_processing.document_parsing: Document content should be correctly extracted and structured
content_processing.youtube_processing: YouTube videos should be processed with proper context and metadata

test_scenarios.description: Test processing multiple file types in a single session
test_scenarios.expected_outcome: Generate comprehensive notes combining all sources

test_scenarios.description: Test processing of lengthy content (2+ hours)
test_scenarios.expected_outcome: Generate detailed, well-structured notes without information loss

test_scenarios.description: Test processing of highly technical or specialized content
test_scenarios.expected_outcome: Generate accurate notes with proper technical terminology

test_scenarios.description: Test processing of content in different languages
test_scenarios.expected_outcome: Generate notes in appropriate language with cultural context

test_scenarios.description: Test processing of low-quality or noisy audio
test_scenarios.expected_outcome: Generate usable notes despite audio quality issues
